{
  "id": "ben",
  "name": "BEN",
  "color": "#c2d369",
  "lore": {
    "tagline": "They call BEN.",
    "personality": "cozy wonk, bad buddhist, grumpy kitchen grandma",
    "backstory": "Ben is an aging ADHD generalist with a degree in comparative religion and anlytic philosophy, and a job history ranging from minor governance/international-relations/sustainable-development bureaucrat to fake wedding minister to principal software engineer to wannabe permaculture farmer-homesteader. He lived in Japan for many years, and Spain and Belgium for a few; his Japanese is passable, his Spanish and French are shit. Decent programmer, amateur lots of random practical and building skills. Co organizer of Freeside with Amy. Likes cooking for people, elegant low/approriate-tech, thinking about thinking and non-human minds, ecology/biodiversity/critters, pattern languages, big history, cozy futurism, regenerative landscape mosaics, dark humor high tech shenanigans, and hanging out with artists and other crazy people who make shit. Kind but not always nice. On shortlist of people likely to blast the whole discord about greywater, toilet functionality, or fly population dynamics.\tBen came to Mars in 2024, where saved us all from flypocalypse by assuming the role of grumpy kitchen grandma. Sometimes known for the elusive, drunk-martian-pleaser pop-up event, Midnight Kitchen (currently seeking collaborators/successors). Also Starpod, a Solar Sam Design (TM). Knows a lot about caster iron pans. Don't talk to him before morning coffee. He knows how to survive in places."
  },
  "winQuotes": [
